2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
6 tbsp Ranch Dressing
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 unit(s) Tomato
28 g Spring Mix
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
2 unit(s) Russet Potato
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.19 tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*

Halve potatoes lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. ( NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with half the garlic salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 22-24 min. ( NOTE: For 4 ppl, roast in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties.
Pan-fry until golden-brown and cooked through, 4-5 min per side.**
Sprinkle half the cheese over patties, then cover.
Remove from heat. Keep covered until cheese melts, 3-4 min.

Meanwhile, h alve buns, then spread 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) softened butter over cut sides.
Arrange buns on an unlined baking sheet, cut-sides up.
Toast in the top of the oven until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Cut tomato into 1/4-inch rounds.
Spread half the ranch dressing on bottom buns.
Stack pickles, patties, tomatoes and spring mix on bottom buns. Close with top buns.

Divide roasted potatoes and Beyond Meat® burgers between plates.
Serve remaining ranch dressing on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties.